The paper deals with safety analysis of autonomous vehicles, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method is based on Hamilton-Jacobi reachability, which is a well-known technique in control theory and optimization, and is often used in robotics and autonomous systems (cs.SY). The method also involves learning-based planning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of vision-based sensors, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
